      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Skin discoloration, warmth, and discharge after surgery can be a normal part of healing for some people. However, those symptoms should not be dismissed, and using Neosporin could potentially mask signs of an infection that could worsen if untreated. Ideally, your doctor will guide you on how to care for your specific situation, but if you're uncertain, bringing your wound in for an evaluation might be the safer choice. I recommend contacting your doctor to discuss your concerns so you can receive personalized advice. It’s always better to err on the side of caution with post-surgical wounds. Please do not delay seeking medical advice if you're concerned about potential infection. Your health and safety should be the top priority.",
