      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get what u mean about being cautious but i'm pretty sure i'm overreacting. it's literally just a tiny bit of yellow liquid, not like a massive amount of pus or anything. if i just use the warm compress to draw it out and keep the neosporin on it, it'll basically be like a localized treatment. i'm not feeling sick or anything, so it can't be that serious, right? i'll just do it tonight and if it's still bad tomorrow i'll call them. it's fine to just try the ointment first?",
