    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's understandable to want to take action and treat the wound yourself, but as a precaution, it's truly better to err on the side of consulting your doctor regarding the symptoms you're experiencing. Your wound needs careful monitoring, especially in the first few days after removal. Minor symptoms like a little bleeding or discharge should always be checked by your healthcare provider to ensure they're not signs of an infection. Skipping a doctor's evaluation is not advisable.\n\nRemember, early detection and treatment are key in preventing complications. You will be fine, but with a little extra caution and prompt communication, you can feel more assured about the healing process. It might be disappointing for you to make another appointment, but your health is worth it. Why not give your doctor a call, explain the situation, and get their opinion? And if they've exited for the day, consider calling the clinic on their behalf or inquiring about their best course of action. Your doctor's advice is invaluable for your specific situation, and they'll help to ensure that your recovery stays on track.",
